law.catch_line: Set fees for noncovered services in participating provider agreement prohibited.
law.text: A participating provider agreement shall not require a participating provider to provide services to an enrolled participant at a fee set by or subject to the approval of the limited health service benefit plan unless the services are covered services under the provider agreement.
law.history: Created 2012 Ky. Acts ch. 116, sec. 10, effective July 12, 2012.
